725557f-a.text:
64th Road, at the northwest corner of Ellwell Crescent, showing two views of the Samuel Waldron farmhouse, built about 1760. 1t is also known as the J. J. Tompkins house, who owned it from 1852 to 1891. Samuel Waldron was born in 1738 and died
in 1799.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  April, 1923

726527f-a.text:
Ellwell Crescent (through front of house when constructed) at 64th Road (along right side of house when constructed), showing in three views the J.J. Tompkins farmhouse, said to have been erected in 1760 by Samuel Waldron. Tompkins estate had control of some
67 acres and this house in u909.
April 1923.
Views 1 and 2
View 3: July 1923.
